"v./n.吵闹，喧哗 【英】 n./v.吵闹，喧哗 (a loud, sustained noise) 【记】 clam(喊)+or 【同】 同根词：proclamatio n(宣言); reclaim(回收，开垦) n. /v. 大的叫喊声(抗议的强烈表示); 大的、持久的噪声 【例】She was clamoring to go to the zoo 她大声吵着要去动物园. 【记】clam喊. 参: claim要求 【参】proclamation(n 宣言); reclaim(v 回收, 开垦); clamorous(adj 吵闹的, 喧哗的) = noisy = vociferous 【记】claim + or 名词 clamor (n.)  late 14c., from Old French clamor ""call, cry, appeal, outcry"" (12c., Modern French clameur), from Latin clamor ""a shout, a loud call"" (either friendly or hostile), from clamare ""to cry out"" (see claim (v.)). clamor (v.)  late 14c., from clamor (n.). Related: Clamored; clamoring."
